<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1436] Using the connectionDotFilePlugin with a Broker not named localhost causes a NullPointerException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1436</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;To recrate, define a broker in your ActiveMQ config file and specify the name, e.g.:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;broker brokerName=&quot;MyBroker&quot; useJmx=&quot;true&quot; persistent=&quot;true&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://activemq.org/config/1.0&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;plugins&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;connectionDotFilePlugin /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/plugins --&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When starting the container a NPE is thrown if no broker called &quot;localhost&quot; is present.  Changing the name of the broker above to &quot;localhost&quot; stops the problem and the .dot files is generated normally.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FYI The problem appears to be in:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   &lt;a href=&quot;http://activemq.apache.org/maven/activemq-core/xref/org/apache/activemq/broker/view/ConnectionDotFileInterceptor.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://activemq.apache.org/maven/activemq-core/xref/org/apache/activemq/broker/view/ConnectionDotFileInterceptor.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...specifically the hardcoded string in this line is in the constuctor:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   ObjectName brokerName = new ObjectName(domain + &quot;:Type=Broker,BrokerName=localhost&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
